### Is this a regression?
Unsure

### Description
The following media queries (in SCSS files) get compiled into incorrect media rules which break the targeting. I have verified this is not coming from SASS and seems to be coming from PostCSS autoprefixer.

```
@media screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 0) and (min-resolution: 0.001dpcm) {
  .something {
    color: red;
  }
}
```
It compiles to:
```
@media screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 0) and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 0), screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 0) and (min-resolution: 0.001dpcm)
.something {
    color: red;
}
```
As a workaround it is possible to stop this behaviour by using `/* autoprefixer: off */` in the file


## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction


- `ng new` select scss as the style format
- Edit src/styles.scss and add the following content
<pre><code>
@media screen and (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 0) and (min-resolution: 0.001dpcm) {
  .something {
    color: red;
  }
}
</code></pre>
- `ng build`
- Inspect the output of dist/\<project\>/styles.css


